nip
Homonym Number: 1
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a standard measure of spirits; a small glass of spirits (occas the approx? 3 fluid ounce glass a `nip' is served in) (cf NOBBLER)
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
